me prescribed times,\nbut a general/daily offerings (with some excep=\r\ntions to avoid on certain\ndays) are also prescribed in scriptures and dharm=\r\na shaastraas which\nusually involve offering water (named tarpaNa) to pitru =\r\ndevataas as a\nreverential homage to them so that they are satiated and get =\r\nliberated\n(ref: 10.015.01 - udiirataamavara utparaasa unmadhyamaaH pitaraH)=\r\n. Agni\nhere is being requested to convey the offering to pitru devataas in\n=\r\nkayva form, we do not know who all pitru devataas that we are karmically\nin=\r\ndebted to but agni knows all of them since agni is also known as\njaatavedaH=\r\n - jaatam sarvam jagad vetti iti jaatavedaaH[the one who knows\nall the crea=\r\nted ones in universe is jaatavedaa].    jaataveda - Rig Veda\nin 6.15.13 say=\r\ns agni is jaataveda because &quot;vishvaa veda janimaa\njaatavedaaH[knowing all c=\r\nreated things and creatures]&quot; and also in the\nsame rik agni is said to be &quot;=\r\ndevaanaam uta yo martyaanaaM yajihThaH sa\nprayajataam[Most skillful worship=\r\nper amidst Gods and mortals, may he\nbegin the sacrifice]&quot;.   Hence we are a=\r\nppeasing and requesting by\nadressing agni as O, jaatavedaH - please convey =\r\nall the oblations to\npitru devataas in-spite of we not knowing them all (th=\r\ne pitru devataas).\n  Agni is said to render the oblations fragrant, fragran=\r\nt to make them\nauspicious. Also pitru devataas consume offerings by smell, =\r\nhence they\ncould have been made/asked to make the offerings fragrant by agn=\r\ni.\n  having requested agni to carry the oblations[kavyaM] to pitru devataas=\r\n,\nand assuming the kavyam is consumed by pitru devataas along with\nsvadha(w=\r\nhich is offered directly) - we are expressing our gratitude and\nthankfulnes=\r\ns to agni by requesting agni to consume the oblation by him\nas well, this i=\r\ns analogous to athithi-satkaara where we attend to all\nguests and offer our=\r\n servings to them, in a similar fashion agni is also\noffered[prayataa - see=\r\n rik 10.015.12 for prayataa] oblations here.\n  references: The Internet, Ve=\r\ndic reader by A.A. MacDonell, Monier\nWilliams andMac Donell dictionaries vi=\r\na Mudgala Ko! sha, Roots and\nVerb-Forms by W.D.Whitney, Vedic Grammar by AA=\r\n MacDonell, Vedic\nMythology by Alfred Hillebrant (translated by Sreeramula =\r\nRajeswara sarma\n- MLBD). Regards,sarma.\n\n\r\n--2-2333485024-8910259741=:4\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=&quot;iso-8859-1&quot;\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;OM guM gurubhyo namaH - gaM gaNapataye namaH - saM saraswatyai namaH .=\r\n.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;Namaste,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; &lt;=\r\nb&gt;Part 12 of 14&lt;/b&gt; -&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; Link to image if you =\r\nwant to have this in devanagari - &nbsp;&lt;a href=3D&quot;http://www.4shared.com/p=\r\nhoto/qjNhLiM9/1001512.html&quot;&gt;http://www.4shared.com/photo/qjNhLiM9/1001512.h=\r\ntml&lt;/a&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; Link to Audio of this rik -&lt;a=\r\n href=3D&quot;http://www.4shared.com/audio/xKHpmlyN/RV101512.html&quot;&gt; http://www.4=\r\nshared.com/audio/xKHpmlyN/RV101512.html&lt;/a&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;=\r\n&nbsp; if there are any mistakes in these translations would request learne=\r\nd ones to please correct and guide.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;##samhitaa##&lt;/=\r\ndiv&gt;&lt;div&gt;tvama&#92;&#39;gna iiLi&#92;_to jaa&#92;&#39;tave&#92;_do.avaa&#92;&#39;DDha&#92;_vyaani&#92;&#39; sura&#92;_bhiiN=\r\ni&#92;&#39; kR^i&#92;_tvii &nbsp;|&#92;&#92;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;praadaaH&#92;&#39; pi&#92;_tR^ibhyaH&#92;&#39; sva&#92;_dhayaa&#92;_=\r\n te a&#92;&#39;kShanna&#92;_ddhi tvaM de&#92;&#39;va&#92;_ praya&#92;&#39;taa ha&#92;_viiMShi&#92;&#39; &nbsp;|| ##10.0=\r\n15.12##&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;##pada##&lt;span class=3D&quot;Apple-tab-span&quot; sty=\r\nle=3D&quot;white-space:pre;&quot;&gt;\t&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;tvam a&#92;_gne&#92;_ ii&#92;_Li&#92;_taH jaa&#92;_t=\r\na&#92;_ve&#92;_daH&#92;_ avaa&#92;&#39;T ha&#92;_vyaani&#92;&#39; su&#92;_ra&#92;_bhiiNi&#92;&#39; kR^i&#92;_tvii &nbsp;|&#92;&#92;&lt;/di=\r\nv&gt;&lt;div&gt;pra a&#92;_daaH&#92;_ pi&#92;_tR^ibhyaH&#92;&#39; sva&#92;_dhayaa&#92;&#39; te a&#92;_kSha&#92;_n a&#92;_ddhi tv=\r\naM de&#92;_va&#92;_ praya&#92;&#39;taa ha&#92;_viiMShi&#92;&#39; &nbsp;|| ##10.015.12##&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;=\r\n/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;##pada2##&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;tvam##You## agne##O, Agni## iiLitaH##having r=\r\nequested by us## jaatavedaH##O Jataveda## avaaT##carry## havyaani##the obla=\r\ntions## surabhiiNi##fragrant## kR^itvii##having made them## &nbsp;|&#92;&#92;&lt;/div&gt;=\r\n&lt;div&gt;pra adaaH##given them## pitR^ibhyaH##to fathers## svadhayaa##with the =\r\nfuneral offering## te##them## akShan##eaten## addhi##eat## tvam##you## deva=\r\n##O, God## pra-yataa##offered## haviiMShi##oblations## &nbsp;|| ##10.015.12=\r\n##&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Translation -&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;O, agni, having r=\r\nequested,O jaatavedaa , have conveyed the oblations having made them fragra=\r\nnt,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;you have presented them (the oblations) to the pitru devataas=\r\n, and with the funeral offerings they have eaten them, now you O God consum=\r\ne the oblations offerred##&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Interpretation -&nbsp;&lt;=\r\n/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; Agni was invoked to come here to the sacrifice site along =\r\nwith the pitru devataas in riks 10.015.09 and 10.015.10, and here is the pl=\r\nace where the actual request of carrying the oblations is being made since =\r\nagni is &quot;kavya-vaahana&quot;, the oblations that are offered to pitru devataas v=\r\nia agni are called kavyaM, and the oblations offered directly to pitru deva=\r\ntaas are called svadha and a ceremony where svadha is offered to pitru deva=\r\ntaas is termed shraaddha. scriptures specify such ceremonies (shraaddha) to=\r\n be performed at some prescribed times, but a general/daily offerings (with=\r\n some exceptions to avoid on certain days) are also prescribed in scripture=\r\ns and dharma shaastraas which usually involve offering water (named tarpaNa=\r\n) to pitru devataas as a reverential homage to them so that they are satiat=\r\ned and get liberated (ref: 10.015.01 - udiirataamavara utparaasa unmadhyama=\r\naH pitaraH).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;Agni here is being requested to convey the off=\r\nering to pitru devataas in kayva form, we do not know who all pitru devataa=\r\ns that we are karmically indebted to but agni knows all of them since agni =\r\nis also known as jaatavedaH - jaatam sarvam jagad vetti iti jaatavedaaH[the=\r\n one who knows all the created ones in universe is jaatavedaa].&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;=\r\n&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; &nbsp;jaataveda - Rig Veda in 6.15.13 says agni is jaataveda be=\r\ncause &quot;vishvaa veda janimaa jaatavedaaH[knowing all created things and crea=\r\ntures]&quot; and also in the same rik agni is said to be &quot;devaanaam uta yo marty=\r\naanaaM yajihThaH sa prayajataam[Most skillful worshipper amidst Gods and mo=\r\nrtals, may he begin the sacrifice]&quot;.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; &nbsp;Hence we are ap=\r\npeasing and requesting by adressing agni as O, jaatavedaH - please convey a=\r\nll the oblations to pitru devataas in-spite of we not knowing them all (the=\r\n pitru devataas). &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;Agni is said=\r\n to render the oblations fragrant, fragrant to make them auspicious. Also p=\r\nitru devataas consume offerings by smell, hence they could have been made/a=\r\nsked to make the offerings fragrant by agni.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp=\r\n;having requested agni to carry the oblations[kavyaM] to pitru devataas, an=\r\nd assuming the kavyam is consumed by pitru devataas along with svadha(which=\r\n is offered directly) - we are expressing our gratitude and thankfulness to=\r\n agni by requesting agni to consume the oblation by him as well, this is an=\r\nalogous to athithi-satkaara where we attend to all guests and offer our ser=\r\nvings to them, in a similar fashion agni is also offered[prayataa - see rik=\r\n 10.015.12 for prayataa] oblations here.&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nb=\r\nsp;references: The Internet, Vedic reader by A.A. MacDonell, Monier William=\r\ns andMac Donell dictionaries via Mudgala Ko! sha, Roots and Verb-Forms by W=\r\n.D.Whitney, Vedic Grammar by AA MacDonell, Vedic Mythology by Alfred Hilleb=\r\nrant (translated by Sreeramula Rajeswara sarma - MLBD).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/d=\r\niv&gt;&lt;div&gt;Regards,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;sarma.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\r\n--2-2333485024-8910259741=:4--\r\n\n"}}